13/11/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The EU will allocate 1m euros to assist Albania's internal financial control of public funds, as part of the Public Internal Financial Control twinning project launched on Tuesday (November 11th). At the kickoff ceremony, the head of the European Commission delegation to Tirana, Helmut Lohan, said that this area needs improvement and that Albania is struggling to show transparency involving taxpayers' money. (Koha Jone, Klan, European Commission official office - 12/11/08)
